everglo ✩ resident floppy fish 2023-03-28 5:35 AM
What I was thinking for this: 1. We choose a base for our #drawthesquad, preferably one with a ton of people. (If we can’t find one to suit our needs, I’m sure one of us can volunteer to draw one!) 2. We number the base as usual, and hold a session where spots get reserved, etc. - only difference between this and a regular #drawthesquad is that after every spot has been filled, we have… 3. Another session where a bunch of us artists will choose which spots we will draw. It might be better to have this session first, so there’s no bias after people’ve reserved spots originally? Anyway- 4. We get down to drawing it. Might be hard to get everything into one final finished piece; we’ll have to figure out a system I think xD That enough detail? :)
